    "Based on these findings, SCM reactivity mechanisms have been categorized into four primary effects: filler effect, nucleation effect, dilution effect, and chemical effect.",
    "The filler effect highlights the ability of SCM particles to occupy voids between cement grains, thereby densifying the concrete microstructure and contributing to improved strength [25].",
    "In addition to strengthening the microstructure, the heat of hydration in cementitious systems is strongly influenced by the proportion of SCMs in the mix.",
    "gel, which further enhances the material's properties.",
    "Moreover, SCMs provide additional nucleation sites that facilitate the formation of hydration products, accelerating the reaction process."
